      "content": "For a high-level corporate executive, I'd say stick to the classic, timeless look of a well-groomed, clean-cut, and polished individual. A well-fitted, navy or charcoal gray three-piece suit, crisp white dress shirt, and a slim tie in muted colors like burgundy or navy are the standard attire for a leadership role. Make sure their hair is neatly combed, and a well-groomed beard or a clean shave is a must. Avoid anything too flashy or attention-seeking, as it may come across as unprofessional.",
